TONIGHT's SHOW MOVED TO STARLINE SOCIAL CLUB: Bells Atlas / Makeunder / Fell Runner
Dustin Moskovitz was invited
18+, $8 adv - $12 door TIX: http://clubleos.com/event.cfm?id=213375&cart pre-purchased tickets will be honored! BELLS ATLAS =========== kaleidosonic soul punch ⚡ afro-soul, rhythm pop-sicles ☄ taste the r'nbow //// missy elliot meets bjork meets the Malian-born love child of david longstreth and annie clark ☀... or something like that "With hypnotic, layered guitars on 'Bling', pitter-patter rhythms on 'Future Bones' and a psychedelic mishmash that Goat would be proud of on 'Sugar for the Queen', the California band sound alluringly exotic. Throw in Sandra Lawson-Ndu's breathy, soulful vocals and they're the complete mystical package." -NME Magazine "Drenched in the echoes of many lovely tones, Bells Atlas‘s new EP Hyperlust is a victory of layered construction. Comprised of four members, all of them steeped in genres like bossa nova, latin psych-rock and African high-life, the group paints canvases of sound on each of the EP’s four tracks, creating a collage of precise guitar, woozy keyboards and wild vocals..." - OKAYPLAYER You can buy HYPERLUST here: https://bellsatlas.bandcamp.com FREE track here: http://hyperlust.bellsatlas.com MAKEUNDER =========== Listen to / read about the Great Headless Blank EP: http://www.npr.org/sections/allsongs/2015/07/09/417727920/read-the-overwhelming-tragic-story-of-makeunders-great-headless-blank-ep "One of the most outstanding and challenging new bits of music I've heard this year [...] I was simply fascinated by a sound filled with choral harmonies and influences that could include Béla Bartók or Ornette Coleman or Talking Heads." - Bob Boilen, NPR Music Led by songwriter Hamilton Ulmer, Makeunder wrestles diverse tastes - from Renaissance motet, to art rock, to 90's R&B, synth pop, soul, & modern orchestral music - into powerful songs about death, survival, migration, & loss. Come ghost-dance to the songs of Great Headless Blank at Leo's Music Club, and help Makeunder celebrate the release! FELL RUNNER ============ Fell Runner is a Los Angeles based rock band that takes inspiration from West African rhythms and melodies. https://www.facebook.com/fellrunnermusic
Saturday, August 22, 2015 at 8:00pm in PDT
